# BitNet-MLX: Nexus Sovereign SDK v10.0.0\
\
**Production-grade, Open-Source-ready Substrate and Vector Architecture for Apple Silicon**\
\
## Mathematical Core\
The runtime layer operates an $a8w1.58$ specification framework. Weight matrices are clamped to absolute-mean ternary boundaries ($\\\{-1, 0, 1\\\}$) scaled by the per-row scalar parameter $\\gamma$, while inputs are projected onto sub-8-bit signed limits:\
$$W_q = \\text\{round\}\\left(\\text\{clip\}\\left(\\frac\{W\}\{\\gamma + \\epsilon\}, -1, 1\\right)\\right)$$\
$$X_q = \\text\{clip\}\\left(\\text\{round\}\\left(X \\times \\frac\{127\}\{\\max(|X|) + \\epsilon\}\\right), -127, 127\\right)$$\
\
Singular Value Decomposition (SVD) pipelines are avoided to keep edge execution at $O(N)$ computational complexity using inline tracking metrics.\
\
